intro: Daucus golickeanus, commonly known as the Golicke's carrot, is a flowering plant native to southern Europe and parts of western Asia. It belongs to the Apiaceae family, which includes other familiar plants like parsley and dill. The plant produces small, yellowish-white flowers arranged in umbels, typical of the family. Its leaves are pinnately lobed, with a slightly hairy texture. The fruit is a dry, two-chambered schizocarp that splits into two one-seeded parts when mature.
